The issue is that when you copy the HTML fragment directly to the clipboard, receiving applications (like Word) often default to Left-to-Right (LTR) if they don't see a full HTML document structure explicitly declaring `dir="rtl"`.

I will fix this by wrapping the copied HTML in a complete "Export Template" with explicit RTL styling for the `<html>`, `<body>`, and a wrapper `<div>`. This forces Word to recognize the content as Hebrew/RTL.

